


## 🔗 Origin vs Upstream (Visual Flow)

Local Repo (your machine)
        |
        | push/pull
        v
   origin (your fork on GitHub)
        |
        | fetch/merge
        v
   upstream (original project repo)

### Explanation:
- **origin** → your fork (default remote when you clone).  
- **upstream** → the original repository you forked from.  
- Workflow:  
  1. You work locally.  
  2. Push changes to **origin** (your fork).  
  3. Periodically fetch updates from **upstream** (the source project).  
  4. Merge upstream changes into your fork, then push back to origin.


